# Individual Signing Up Page
individual.signing-up.heading                                           = Signing up for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax
individual.signing-up.header-section.para-1                             = Making Tax Digital for Income Tax is a new way of reporting income to HMRC. It’s currently in a voluntary phase for selected self-employed businesses and landlords.
individual.signing-up.header-section.inset.para-1                       = Signing up for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax is voluntary at the moment. However, if your total qualifying income is more than:
individual.signing-up.header-section.inset.bullet-1                     = £50,000 or more for April 2026
individual.signing-up.header-section.inset.bullet-2                     = £30,000 or more for April 2027
individual.signing-up.header-section.para-2                             = You may be able to sign up for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax if you:
individual.signing-up.header-section.bullet-1                           = are a sole trader
individual.signing-up.header-section.bullet-2                           = receive income from property
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.heading                            = How to sign up
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.check-eligibility.heading          = Check if you can sign up
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.check-eligibility.para             = Answer the questions to find out if you may be eligible.
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.heading               = Sign in to your HMRC account
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.para1                 = If you find out you may be eligible, sign in to your HMRC account.
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.para2                 = Depending on your circumstances, you will be offered to sign up for the:
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.bullet1               = current tax year ({0} to {1})
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.bullet2               = next tax year ({0} to {1})
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.inset-para            = There may be circumstances which stop you from using Making Tax Digital for Income Tax at the moment. These may include certain other incomes or activities, or the length of time you’ve been self-employed.
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.hmrc-account.after-inset-para      = If you’re not eligible for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax yet, continue to submit your annual Self Assessment as normal.
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.complete-sign-up.heading           = Complete sign-up tasks
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.complete-sign-up.para              = To sign up you need to:
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.complete-sign-up.bullet1           = add any sole trader or UK and foreign property business income
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.complete-sign-up.bullet2           = select which year you want to start using Making Tax Digital for Income Tax
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.sign-up.heading                    = Sign up
individual.signing-up.how-to-sign-up.sign-up.para                       = You’ll be told you have successfully signed up for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax.

## Accounting period check
accounting-period-check.heading                                         = What accounting period do you use for your business?
accounting-period-check.caption                                         = Eligibility questions
accounting-period-check.para                                            = This is the accounting period you use each year when reporting your business income and expenses to HMRC.
accounting-period-check.hint                                            = For example, your business accounting period might start on 6 April and end on 5 April of the following year (such as, 6 April 2026 to 5 April 2027).
accounting-period-check.sixth-april-to-fifth-april                      = 6 April to 5 April
accounting-period-check.first-april-to-thirty-first-march               = 1 April to 31 March
accounting-period-check.other                                           = Neither of these
accounting-period-check.error                                           = Select your business accounting period, or select ‘Neither of these’

## Cannot Sign Up Page
cannot-sign-up.heading                                                  = You cannot sign up yet
cannot-sign-up.para-one                                                 = Your business does not use an accounting period that runs from either:
cannot-sign-up.bullet-one                                               = 1 April to 31 March
cannot-sign-up.bullet-two                                               = 6 April to 5 April
cannot-sign-up.para-two                                                 = Making Tax Digital for Income Tax is only available to people who use these business accounting periods.
cannot-sign-up.para-three                                               = In the future, we may extend this service to more people.
cannot-sign-up.send-self-assessment                                     = Continue submitting your {0} as normal.
cannot-sign-up.send-self-assessment.link                                = Self Assessment tax return

